{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12ac80bb-4097-4904-bd6e-44257b4cea34","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project too:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88d65008-efd6-4335-b21d-1e4ea8e613c0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":198,"requestId":"7C1A:16E90D:2683010:2AD4AEF:69F946E2"},"id":"c1673df0-9237-4c26-a736-bc4620cb342a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:24:54.623Z","parentId":"ea170446-442e-4687-b011-20a5028a43bf"}
